### Top 20 Recon-ng Commands and Their Explanations

Recon-ng is packed with powerful commands for various reconnaissance tasks. Here are the top 20 commands you should know:

1. **`workspaces list`**
     ell
   workspaces list
   *Lists all existing workspaces.*

2. **`workspaces create <name>`**
     ell
   workspaces create my_workspace
   *Creates a new workspace named "my_workspace".*

3. **`workspaces select <name>`**
     ell
   workspaces select my_workspace
   *Selects an existing workspace named "my_workspace".*

4. **`workspaces delete <name>`**
     ell
   workspaces delete my_workspace
   *Deletes an existing workspace named "my_workspace".*

5. **` ow modules`**
     ell
    ow modules
   *Displays all available modules.*

6. **`use <module_name>`**
     ell
   use recon/domains-hosts/google_site_web
   *Loads the specified module.*

7. **` ow options`**
     ell
    ow options
   *Displays the options for the loaded module.*

8. **`set <option> <value>`**
     ell
   set source example.com
   *Sets the specified option to the given value.*

9. **`run`**
     ell
   run
   *Executes the loaded module.*

10. **` ow hosts`**
      ell
     ow hosts
    *Displays the discovered hosts.*

11. **`add domains <domain>`**
      ell
    add domains example.com
    *Adds a domain to the target list.*

12. **`add hosts <host>`**
      ell
    add hosts 192.168.1.1
    *Adds a host to the target list.*

13. **`add contacts <contact>`**
      ell
    add contacts admin@example.com
    *Adds a contact to the target list.*

14. **`add companies <company>`**
      ell
    add companies ExampleCorp
    *Adds a company to the target list.*

15. **` ow domains`**
      ell
     ow domains
    *Displays the added domains.*

16. **` ow contacts`**
      ell
     ow contacts
    *Displays the added contacts.*

17. **` ow companies`**
      ell
     ow companies
    *Displays the added companies.*

18. **`info`**
      ell
    info
    *Displays information about the loaded module.*

19. **`search <query>`**
      ell
    search google
    *Searches for modules matching the query.*

20. **`exit`**
      ell
    exit
    *Exits the Recon-ng console.*

These commands will help you efficiently navigate and utilize Recon-ng for your reconnaissance tasks. Each command plays a crucial role in managing workspaces, loading and running modules, and displaying or adding target information.
